Version 4.99b: Summary of major changes (minor update only)
**************************************************************************

Improvements to plrender and near-completion of Amiga drivers.  

**************************************************************************
Version 4.99a: Summary of major changes
**************************************************************************

o Plplot now requires an ANSI compliant compiler.

o Internally massively restructured, many variables/functions localized to a
single file and made static, number of source files greatly reduced.

o Command-line parsing utilities added, so that many PLPLOT internal
variables can be set from the command line (from C or C++ only).  See
plrender.c or the C example programs for example usage.

o User-installable keyboard event handler support added, so user codes can
get and react to user input.  See plrender.c for example usage.

o Plrender now supports page seeks from the xwindow, xterm, and Amiga drivers
(all except xterm honor backspace as a page-backward key).  Note: as a result
of this change, old metafiles have all seeking (-b, -e, -p flags) disabled.
You can render them into new format metafiles to take advantage of the new
capabilities.

o Font files are now system-independent.

o X-window driver now refreshes and resizes.

o New contour functions (from C) now accept function pointers instead of
array pointers, allowing the user to determine the memory organization
of 2-d arrays.

o Bug fixes to various drivers (orientation should always work now, LaserJet
driver fixed, etc.).

o New driver: null device.

o Now possible to change the string escape character to any of [!#$%&*@^~].

o Polylines (solid only) now supported by all drivers and line plot commands.

o Support for color postscript added.

